# Use Base UI for all interactive primitives

When building any interactive UI component (tooltip, dialog, menu, popover, select, accordion, tabs, etc.), **always** use `@base-ui-components/react` instead of rolling custom implementations with manual state, portals, or positioning logic.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — use Base UI
import { Tooltip } from "@base-ui-components/react/tooltip";

// ❌ BAD — custom tooltip with manual portals/positioning
import { createPortal } from "react-dom";
function MyTooltip() { /* manual getBoundingClientRect, useState, etc. */ }
```

Base UI provides accessible, headless primitives that handle focus management, keyboard navigation, positioning, and portaling correctly. Style them with Tailwind — do not reimplement these behaviors from scratch.
